      "content": {
        "title": "Celiac Disease Malabsorption",
        "definition": "Autoimmune gluten sensitivity damaging small intestinal villi, reducing absorptive surface and causing malabsorption of fats, vitamins, and minerals.",
        "summary": "Anti-tTG antibodies are diagnostic. Villous atrophy on biopsy confirms. Gluten-free diet is treatment."
      },
